The paper deals with named entity recognition (NER) using neural networks and byte-pair encodings (BPE) on biomedical datasets. This falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML), which are covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as it specifically deals with NLP. cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories as they cover ML techniques. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible category as the paper uses neural networks. Finally, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with text classification.
